5. Formal Model

Let organism state at time t be:

O(t) = [A, R, M, I, P, H, B]

Where:
	•	A = attention allocation
	•	R = arousal/regulation state
	•	M = meaning load
	•	I = identity/self-model
	•	P = prediction/confidence
	•	H = hormone-relevant physiological readiness
	•	B = behavior output

Let simulation input be:

S(t) = [fidelity, immersion, relevance, emotional charge, agency, repeatability]

Then the effect of simulation can be modeled as:

Delta O = T(S, context, body_state, history)

Where T is a transformation operator shaped by:
	•	current stress
	•	prior conditioning
	•	environment
	•	belief
	•	training status
	•	realism of simulation

Growth occurs when repeated simulation alters behavior and physiology enough to change adaptation over time:

Growth ~= integral(Behavior x Recovery x Meaning x Consistency) dt

