9. The “Astral Projection” UI Framing

In Pantheon/Atlas terms, “astral projection” is defined as:

The immersive experience of navigating a structured simulation space with sufficient fidelity and agency that it feels spatially real to the user.

This is not a supernatural claim.
It is a model-navigation interface.

Characteristics
	•	high spatialization of abstract data
	•	embodied navigation of symbolic terrain
	•	identity continuity across sessions
	•	interaction with modeled systems, not physical displacement

Uses
	•	strategy
	•	learning
	•	healing rehearsal
	•	planning
	•	cultural exploration
	•	simulated world-building
	•	decision preview

