10. Growth Formula

A simple operational version:

Growth = fidelity x emotional salience x repetition x action transfer x recovery compatibility

Where:
	•	fidelity = how well the simulation matches the target domain
	•	emotional salience = how much it matters to the organism
	•	repetition = sufficient exposure for encoding
	•	action transfer = how much simulated training changes real behavior
	•	recovery compatibility = whether it supports rather than overloads the system

If action transfer is near zero, the growth effect is limited.

