12. Failure Modes

12.1 Substitution Error

Mistaking simulation for sufficient reality.
Example:
	•	visualizing training instead of training

12.2 Dissociation Drift

The user becomes more attached to the simulation than to external calibration.

12.3 Fidelity Collapse

The simulation becomes aesthetically strong but operationally false.

12.4 Overarousal

Too much immersion creates anxiety, sleep disruption, or stress overload.

12.5 Narrative Hijack

The meaning layer becomes manipulative, grandiose, or detached from reality testing.

