13. Guardrails
	•	simulation must remain linked to reality testing
	•	internal model space must not be confused with external fact
	•	immersive states need clear entry/exit boundaries
	•	do not replace medical, physical, or relational realities with modeled substitutes
	•	preserve reversibility
	•	dose by phase, not by novelty
	•	measure transfer, not just feeling

⸻

14. Design Rule

The best simulation is not the one that feels most magical.
It is the one that most reliably transfers into better real-world adaptation.

⸻

15. Compression

Simulation works when it:
	•	makes meaning vivid
	•	changes state
	•	improves behavior
	•	supports physiology
	•	transfers into reality

It fails when it:
	•	replaces reality
	•	inflates certainty
	•	breaks grounding
	•	produces emotion without adaptation

